l analyses and case studies. Using numerous examples that focus on North America, Europe, Central Asia, and the Middle East, this book considers strategies and incentives that help lessen conflict and motivate cooperation under scarcity and increased variability of water resources.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aWater securityxSocial aspects. 0aWater-supplyxInternational cooperation. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aarmed conflict.  acase studies.  acentral asia.  aclimate change.  aclimatology.  aconflict resolution.  acooperation.  aecology.  aenvironmental changes.  aeurope.  aglobal warming.  aglobalization.  agovernment and governing.  ainternational water management.  amedia coverage.  amiddle east.  anatural resource shortages.  anatural resources.  anorth america.  apeaceful dispute resolution.  apolitical boundaries.  apolitical.  awar.  awater paucity.  awater resources.  awater scarcity.  awater variability.  awater.1 aDinar, Ariel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052028307740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520958906423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520958906/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles